The paper deals with deep convolutional networks for image generation and restoration, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the ability of a randomly-initialized neural network to capture low-level image statistics, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks to diagnose and restore images, which is related to neural engineering (cs.NE) and information theory (cs.IT).
